This article describes how to enable the macro keys on the Logitech G105 keyboard using sidewinderd. In addition to the Logitech G105, sidewinderd also supports the Logitech G710, Logitech G710+, Microsoft SideWinder X4 and Microsoft SideWinder X6 keyboards.

== Hardware ==

{{Cmd|lsusb|output=<pre>
046d:c248 Logitech, Inc. G105 Gaming Keyboard
</pre>}}

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===

{{KernelBox|title=User level driver support|
    Device Drivers --->
          Input device support --->
            [*]   Miscellaneous devices --->
                    <*>   User level driver support
}}

=== Software ===

sidewinderd needs to be built manually since no ebuild is available in the Portage tree. First, create a directory to hold the sidewinderd source code:

{{RootCmd
|mkdir -p /usr/local/src
|cd /usr/local/src
}}

Clone the sidewinderd Git repository (requires {{Package|dev-vcs/git}}):

{{RootCmd|git clone <nowiki>https://github.com/tolga9009/sidewinderd.git</nowiki>}}

Install the required dependencies:

{{Emerge
|cmake libconfig tinyxml2
|params+=--noreplace
}}

Build and install sidewinderd:

{{RootCmd
|cd sidewinderd
|mkdir build
|cd build
|cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH{{=}}/usr ..
|make
|make install
}}

== Configuration ==

Specify the username to run sidewinderd as:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/sidewinderd.conf|
user {{=}} "larry";
}}

{{Important|It highly recommended to '''''not''''' run sidewinderd as {{c|root}}.}}

To record macros without delays set <var>capture_delays</var> to <code>false</code>:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/sidewinderd.conf|
capture_delays {{=}} false;
}}

=== Service ===

==== OpenRC ====

Create the following init.d file:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/init.d/sidewinderd|lang=bash|
#!/sbin/openrc-run

command{{=}}"/usr/bin/sidewinderd"
command_args{{=}}"-c /etc/sidewinderd.conf -d"
}}

Start sidewinderd:

{{RootCmd|rc-service sidewinderd start}}

Start sidewinderd at boot:

{{RootCmd|rc-update add sidewinderd default}}

==== systemd ====

Start sidewinderd:

{{RootCmd|systemctl start sidewinderd}}

Start sidewinderd at boot:

{{RootCmd|systemctl enable sidewinderd}}

== Usage ==

If sidewinderd started successfully, the {{Key|MR}}, {{Key|M1}}, {{Key|M2}}, {{Key|M3}} and {{Key|G1}} through {{Key|G6}} keys should now be usable. Three sets of macro profiles can be switched between using the {{Key|M1}}, {{Key|M2}} and {{Key|M3}} keys. Recorded macros are stored in their respective profile directories i.e. {{Path|~/.local/share/sidewinderd/profile_{1,2,3}}}

To record a macro for the {{Key|G1}} key in the {{Key|M1}} profile, press {{Key|M1}}, {{Key|MR}}, {{Key|G1}}, the desired key sequence, and {{Key|MR}} again. To playback the recorded macro, press the {{Key|G1}} key.

== Removal ==

To uninstall sidewinderd, delete the following files:

{{RootCmd
|rm /etc/init.d/sidewinderd
|rm /etc/sidewinderd.conf
|rm /usr/bin/sidewinderd
|rm /usr/lib/systemd/system/sidewinderd.service
}}

